    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-28T10:29:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-28T10:29:00-05:00" n="128"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d128">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/1383</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Francis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vologda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-28T18:00:00+02:31">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 28, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 7.40 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>40. Answering your 23, March 25, 5 p.m., via Vladivostok, received March 26, 11
                    p.m. Received Siberian delegation in January who claimed were forming separate
                    Siberian government and would advise when organized by assembly called March 10,
                    and as cabled Department. Reported assembly failed to materialize. Present
                    government claims undisputed jurisdiction throughout Siberia. This exactly what
                    sent <persName corresp="#p_HWC1">Huntington</persName>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d128fn1">
                        <persName corresp="#p_HWC1">William C. Huntington</persName>, Commercial
                        Attaché.</note> to investigate and report but notwithstanding he arrived
                    Irkutsk certainly March 10, no report received. <persName corresp="#p_WJB1"
                        >Wright</persName> left Irkutsk 17th after staying two days, nothing from
                    him since leaving Vologda. <persName corresp="#p_MDB1">Macgowan</persName>’s <hi
                        rend="italic">en clair</hi> telegrams received two days after filing and
                    report <persName corresp="#p_HWC1">Huntington</persName> and
                        <persName>Thomas</persName>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d128fn2">
                        <persName>Edward B. Thomas</persName>, attached to the office of the
                        Commercial Attaché.</note> efficiently assisting and <persName
                        corresp="#p_HWC1">Huntington</persName> awaiting instructions from <persName
                        corresp="#p_RWC1">Redfield</persName> concerning self and
                        <persName>Thomas</persName> whom I requested for Embassy service Vologda. Am
                    wiring them daily. Been there month. Reported nothing about new government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_FDR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
